07/02/2007
ZAGREB, Croatia -- European Commission (EC) Ambassador to Zagreb Vincent Degert said on Tuesday (February 6th) that Croatia could open talks on a few more chapters of the acquis over the next couple of weeks.
As of now, five chapters have been opened, talks on two have been completed, and positions on nine others have been presented.
There are 33 in all.
Degert also called on the Croatian government to step up administrative reforms, to more easily achieve EU membership.
(Poslovni dnevnik, Vjesnik - 07/02/07;
HINA, HRT - 06/02/07)
